<item>
            <title>[SEC-646] can&apos;t get @Secured annotations to work  using spring-security in a spring-2.5 app</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-646</link>
                <project id="10040" key="SEC">Spring Security</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m using &amp;lt;security:annotation-driven/&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here is the error message :&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;22:35:21&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;WARN  &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;AbstractSecurityInterceptor&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; Could not validate configuration attributes as the ObjectDefinitionSource did not return a ConfigAttributeDefinition Iterator&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;NOTE : There is a binary incompatability between spring-security between spring 2.0 and spring-2.5.  Rather than compiling spring-security against the spring-2.5 jars I made a patch to change spring-security so that when compiled against spring-2.0, it is binary compatible with spring-2.5.  See &lt;a href=&quot;http://jira.springframework.org/browse/SEC-627&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://jira.springframework.org/browse/SEC-627&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you apply the patch on that task, you can get spring-security running with spring 2.5, then you can run my demo app which I will attach in a zip&lt;/p&gt;</description>
