                            <comment id="32080" author="luke" created="Thu, 14 Feb 2008 23:25:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Could you clarify whether this works if the binary incompatibility is fixed, or if this is a separate issue?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="33161" author="luke" created="Tue, 11 Mar 2008 05:26:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This looks like a potential duplicate of two other issues &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-713&quot; title=&quot;Annotation-driven security fails when using Spring &amp;gt; 2.0.6&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SEC-713&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SEC-713&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-429&quot; title=&quot;@Secured on implementation classes&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SEC-429&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SEC-429&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="33192" author="luke" created="Tue, 11 Mar 2008 23:11:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The annotation unit tests are now running successfully with 2.5.2 following the fix for &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-713&quot; title=&quot;Annotation-driven security fails when using Spring &amp;gt; 2.0.6&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SEC-713&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SEC-713&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, so I&apos;m closing this. If there are still problems which can be demonstrated to work wth 2.0 but not 2.5 please open a separate issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="126644" author="issuemaster" created="Sat, 6 Feb 2016 06:34:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue has been migrated to &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-security/issues/907&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-security/issues/907&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
